hed up my levels to 60 with my Bard.<br><br>3-I was in 45, and the rumor of hell levels being removed was a hot topic. So I figured wny not wait, its just another reason.<br><br>----<br><br>After talking with the BLs in the guild last night (both level 60 with ntov loot or better) they said now was the time to return.<br><br>My question is why? They were busy with a ntov raid (as was I and couldnt' talk for twisting). So I'm here asking you all now what is different now that is so much better than before? What imporovements will I have on my level 45 BL now that I wouldn't have when I stopped playing him 4 months ago?<br><br>Spells? Abilities (I remember double attack was a big one folks wanted)? Alternate Advancement? Soloability now compared to pre-patch on the 26? Raid effective ness now compared to pre 26th patch? <p><CENTER><table border=1>     <tr>     <td><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10808" target="Jondin's Profile"><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/klangston/signature/Jondin_Sig.JPG"></a></td>     </tr>     </table></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uvecsusbst.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VecsusBST</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Savage Hunter</span><br>  Posts: 602<br> <font color=#FF9933>(10/1/02 8:44:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3785.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Now is the Time to Play a Beastlord?</span><hr size=1> the class is just as playable now as it was 3, 5, or 10 months ago.  EQ is what you make of it.  There will never be a perfect class.<br><br>Recent improvements include:<br>-  AAs, <br>-  more gear with the BST tag added to it.<br>-  VI has shown they are aware of our pet damage issues and is working to fix it.<br>-  Spell upgrades<br>-  I think the best improvement in the class is that there are finally people that are getting used to us being around.  3 months ago hardly anyone knew that Purity was a spell and that it would stack with Clarity/Bard song.  Give people a taste for what a beastlord brings to the group and they will grow to accept us and even seek us out for groups/raids.<br><br>So the short answer is:  a good time to come back would have been 10 minutes after you left. <p>Vecsus Strangiato <br>Level 94 Beastlord <br>Tarew Marr <br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=212314>My Magelo</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uvadorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vadorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beastling</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#FF9933>(10/1/02 9:32:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3785.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.digital-jay.com/head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Now is the Time to Play a Beastlord?</span><hr size=1> Vecsus is *such* a romantic. rofl. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ujurath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jurath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#FF9933>(10/1/02 10:25:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3785.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Now is the Time to Play a Beastlord?</span><hr size=1> Why would anyone play a beastlord?<br><br>The answer is simple, if you have more fun playing a beastlord than your bard then play a beasty, if not then don't.<br><br>Beastlords do have a very bright future, it may take us a while find our place in eq but to be honest it's the *not knowing* that makes this class exciting right now.<br><br>No other class in eq is as incomplete as the beastlord, we are on the verge of finding our purpose and raison d'etre, we may even have already been given that purpose in the recent aa skills and don't realise it yet.<br><br>It's almost like puberty, we're going through some huge changes that confuse us, frustrate us, even anger us and the desire to become a complete and &quot;adult&quot; class is overwhelming.  We are evolving, we may end up as something none of us could foresee, that's why I keep playing, just to see where it goes.<br><br>Life isn't about the destination, it's about the journey....and beer is good.....k thx come again.<br><br> <p><img src="http://www.vickye.fsnet.co.uk/images/jsig.jpg" border="0"> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/usabousa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sabousa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beastling</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#FF9933>(10/1/02 12:27:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3785.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Now is the Time to Play a Beastlord?</span><hr size=1>  I see good things comming from the new pet. I have no way to back it up. but there sure not going to try another warder with 2 broken legs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1